One tap and a piece of paper with a number comes out of the machine.
You can't even read "157" and your number is already beeping on the big display under the ceiling of the waiting room.
In half a second, it's your turn.
An older married couple comes to ask about the lease after a while, but the rush in the waiting room obviously does not apply to new leases at all.
Most people came to solve common problems as usual - requests for repairs, insurance claims and the like.
