"No one's going to be judged here," one of Byty's RPG employees thinks, and the man on the street outside the client center gives her a partial account.
“I have $13,000 in retirement and I have $5,000 left to eat, I don’t have the money to sue,” he said.
However, the workers soon become insecure.
"We'll see."
